WEBVTT

00:01.250 --> 00:03.120
Delilah: There's something
we need to talk about.

00:03.120 --> 00:04.790
It's about Charlie and me.

00:04.790 --> 00:07.040
Eddie:
We all want to believe we have
control over our lives.

00:07.040 --> 00:09.250
You spoke
at his funeral!

00:09.250 --> 00:11.080
I trusted you!

00:11.080 --> 00:12.880
But that's rarely the case.

00:12.880 --> 00:14.500
Delilah:
Take care of her.
We will.

00:14.500 --> 00:16.170
Everything keeps changing.

00:16.170 --> 00:17.670
Stability is fleeting.

00:17.670 --> 00:20.920
I think he's struggling.
A new baby half-sister.

00:20.920 --> 00:22.380
Despite our best efforts...

00:22.380 --> 00:25.000
You keep saying you need to know
who you are without cancer.

00:25.000 --> 00:27.330
Maybe I need to figure out
who I am without you.

00:27.330 --> 00:28.580
...things change...

00:28.580 --> 00:30.080
Are you --
Are you s-saying --

00:30.080 --> 00:32.540
I want
to adopt a baby.
[ Chuckles ]

00:32.540 --> 00:34.170
...our perspectives shift...

00:34.170 --> 00:35.250
I didn't give you
what you needed.

00:35.250 --> 00:37.500
So you had to go
get it from...Eric.

00:37.500 --> 00:39.540
...and we just have to keep up.

00:39.540 --> 00:41.250
Gary,
this is not on you.

00:41.250 --> 00:43.170
I could've
handled myself better.

00:43.170 --> 00:48.460
♪♪

00:48.460 --> 00:50.040
You know, bud,
I was thinking...

00:50.040 --> 00:51.750
we don't have to do this
every day.

00:51.750 --> 00:53.080
We could do this...

00:53.080 --> 00:55.920
every other day,
every third day.

00:55.920 --> 00:57.830
Maggie:
Oh! There's my guy!

00:57.830 --> 00:59.250
I missed you!

00:59.250 --> 01:00.330
[ Colin barks ]

01:00.330 --> 01:02.000
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, hey.

01:03.500 --> 01:04.580
Hey!

01:06.330 --> 01:09.000
Gary. You're running.
[ Sighs ]

01:09.000 --> 01:12.040
I thought one of your hobbies
was, uh, not running.

01:12.040 --> 01:14.830
Yeah. Well...helping Colin
get back in shape.

01:14.830 --> 01:16.460
He's getting
a little flabby.

01:16.460 --> 01:19.000
He keeps trying to
convince me it's puppy fat,
but we all know the truth.

01:19.000 --> 01:20.830
Man: Watch out!
Coming through!

01:20.830 --> 01:22.670
Ugh.
I hate those things.
I hate those things.

01:23.620 --> 01:24.710
[ Chuckles ]

01:24.710 --> 01:26.790
Eh...guess it's good
for the environment.

01:26.790 --> 01:27.830
Mm.

01:27.830 --> 01:29.790
It's not worth it.
It's not worth it.

01:32.710 --> 01:34.750
Oh, uh,
Elena reached out.

01:34.750 --> 01:36.250
She said that
you're the only one

01:36.250 --> 01:38.830
who hasn't RSVP'd
to her remission party.

01:38.830 --> 01:40.210
Yeah, I've been
putting off responding

01:40.210 --> 01:42.330
'cause of the whole you
and...you know...

01:42.330 --> 01:44.080
Oh. Yeah.
I mean -- Don't worry.

01:44.080 --> 01:46.580
Everybody in the group knows
that we broke up. [ Chuckles ]

01:46.580 --> 01:49.420
Hence my reluctance to attend
the festivities today.

01:49.420 --> 01:51.580
I mean, I like a cancer-themed
party as much as the next guy,

01:51.580 --> 01:53.750
but I'm not sure
I can endure two hours of

01:53.750 --> 01:55.080
"Oh, what happened?"

01:55.080 --> 01:57.420
I know. But I just want
to support Elena.

01:57.420 --> 02:00.170
Five years of remission
is a big deal.

02:00.170 --> 02:03.670
Also, they got a private room
at the Top of the Hub,

02:03.670 --> 02:04.750
which is closing soon.

02:04.750 --> 02:06.920
It would mean a lot
to Elena.

02:06.920 --> 02:08.500
You're right.

02:08.500 --> 02:09.880
I'll go.
I'll be there.

02:09.880 --> 02:11.000
[ Chuckling ]
Okay. Great.

02:11.000 --> 02:13.170
Well, then,
I guess I'll see you there.

02:13.170 --> 02:16.790
Um...do you guys
wanna join me?

02:16.790 --> 02:18.170
I've got
about two miles left.

02:18.170 --> 02:19.880
Left?

02:19.880 --> 02:23.670
Hooh. You know,
if it was just me, hells yeah.

02:23.670 --> 02:27.500
But, uh...that's a lot
of running for the big fella.

02:27.500 --> 02:30.460
Don't -- Don't wanna push it
with the dog.
No.

02:30.460 --> 02:32.880
Bye, Colin!

02:32.880 --> 02:38.790
♪♪

02:38.790 --> 02:41.880
[ Door closes ]
Lenny:
I'm glad you're finally driving
a nice, big, safe car.

02:41.880 --> 02:44.290
You can't be too careful
with this little passenger.

02:44.290 --> 02:46.500
I've had that car
for a while.

02:46.500 --> 02:49.290
Remember, Dad? Jon got it for me
for my birthday last year.

02:49.290 --> 02:50.830
Oh, yeah. Right.

02:50.830 --> 02:52.460
I love this place.

02:52.460 --> 02:56.380
It is so much brighter
than your old apartment.

02:56.380 --> 02:58.540
And it's nice to know
that people are here

02:58.540 --> 03:00.000
to check in on you.

03:00.000 --> 03:02.420
You know what they're serving
in the dining hall tonight?

03:02.420 --> 03:04.080
Turkey meatloaf.

03:04.080 --> 03:05.580
On a Friday.

03:05.580 --> 03:08.460
How dare they not know
about Pizza Friday.

03:08.460 --> 03:09.960
[ Refrigerator door opens ]

03:09.960 --> 03:11.210
So, how you doing,
DeeDee?

03:11.210 --> 03:13.710
I mean, other than
having to deal with

03:13.710 --> 03:15.670
your prince
of a father.

03:16.670 --> 03:18.830
I'm good.

03:18.830 --> 03:21.330
The house is too quiet
without Sophie there.

03:21.330 --> 03:23.540
Well, at least you have little
Danny here to keep you company.

03:23.540 --> 03:25.120
♪♪

03:25.120 --> 03:27.040
It's Charlie, Dad.

03:27.040 --> 03:30.170
Oh, right. Right, right.
Of course. Of course.

03:30.170 --> 03:31.790
[ Coos ]
I don't know
if you're aware,

03:31.790 --> 03:33.880
but I have
a slight memory problem.

03:33.880 --> 03:35.580
[ Chuckles ]

03:35.580 --> 03:37.670
Yet you don't let it
get you down.

03:37.670 --> 03:40.290
It's like
that story you tell

03:40.290 --> 03:42.880
about the young sergeant
in love.

03:44.080 --> 03:45.750
Oh...yeah.

03:45.750 --> 03:46.790
Right.

03:46.790 --> 03:50.250
♪♪

03:50.250 --> 03:52.880
W-What was that, again?

03:54.830 --> 03:58.040
Nothing.

03:58.040 --> 04:00.500
Help me out here,
Charlie.

04:00.500 --> 04:01.670
[ Chuckles ]

04:01.670 --> 04:03.920
♪♪

04:12.330 --> 04:14.830
[ Laughs ] I know, Mom.
Us, too.

04:14.830 --> 04:16.170
[ Chuckles ]
What did she say?

04:16.170 --> 04:17.670
She said she's excited.

04:17.670 --> 04:19.170
Of course she's excited!
It's exciting!

04:19.170 --> 04:20.750
She's about to be
a grandma!

04:20.750 --> 04:21.880
Oh, uh, yeah.

04:21.880 --> 04:23.420
Eve is eight and a half months
pregnant.

04:23.420 --> 04:25.960
Tell her the baby's
the size of a large cabbage.

04:25.960 --> 04:27.290
I've been reading up.

04:27.290 --> 04:28.750
About babies,
not cabbages.

04:28.750 --> 04:30.000
Mm. No, I --

04:30.000 --> 04:32.790
Mom, slow down.
Nothing has happened yet.

04:32.790 --> 04:33.880
[ Chuckles ]

04:33.880 --> 04:35.790
Well, we're just gonna
meet each other,

04:35.790 --> 04:37.420
see if
we're the right fit.

04:37.420 --> 04:40.210
It's -- It's an interview --
for all of us.

04:40.210 --> 04:42.670
Tell your mom
Eve's got kind eyes.

04:42.670 --> 04:44.830
She heard you. She said eyes are
the windows to the soul.

04:44.830 --> 04:46.120
She gets it.

04:46.120 --> 04:47.580
And let her know this doesn't
usually happen this quickly.

04:47.580 --> 04:48.670
You want
to talk to her?

04:48.670 --> 04:50.830
No.
She called you.

04:50.830 --> 04:52.290
Mm-hmm.

04:53.330 --> 04:55.210
Theo! Let's go!

04:55.210 --> 04:56.460
Breakfast!

04:56.460 --> 04:58.500
Did he mention it
when you woke him up?

04:58.500 --> 05:00.000
No.
He seemed fine.

05:00.000 --> 05:01.920
I think we handled it
the right way --

05:01.920 --> 05:04.380
just, you know,
not making a big deal out of it.

05:04.380 --> 05:07.000
Yeah. "Even though we tell you
never to talk to strangers,

05:07.000 --> 05:09.670
we're gonna pay one to talk to
you about how you're feeling."

05:09.670 --> 05:10.750
Yeah, right.
[ Water running ]

05:10.750 --> 05:12.000
"And look --
[ Water stops ]

05:12.000 --> 05:15.040
waffles with a disgusting amount
of chocolate chips.

05:15.040 --> 05:16.670
Gonna be a good day."

05:16.670 --> 05:18.380
There he is!

05:18.380 --> 05:20.500
Chocolate chip waffles
on a weekday?

05:20.500 --> 05:21.750
It's like they say, bud,

05:21.750 --> 05:23.750
breakfast is the most important
dessert of the day.

05:23.750 --> 05:25.960
[ Chuckles ]
That's right.

05:29.880 --> 05:32.250
So, what is on
everyone's schedule for today?

05:32.250 --> 05:34.750
Ah, well, Liam's mom and I
are still trying

05:34.750 --> 05:37.330
to set up a playdate
for after school.

05:37.330 --> 05:39.580
Oh, and, uh,
we have that appointment

05:39.580 --> 05:41.420
with Susan this morning.

05:41.420 --> 05:42.750
Oh, yeah.

05:42.750 --> 05:45.170
I'm not going to that.

05:45.170 --> 05:50.170
♪♪

05:50.170 --> 05:52.500
Delilah: It's just hard,
seeing my dad like that.

05:52.500 --> 05:55.250
I'll think I'm used to it,
and then -- pshew! --

05:55.250 --> 05:56.750
there's s-something else,

05:56.750 --> 06:00.000
another piece of him
that disappears.

06:00.000 --> 06:01.880
I'll take care of that,
Jake.

06:01.880 --> 06:03.750
For as long
as I can remember,

06:03.750 --> 06:06.120
he's had
these twelve stories,

06:06.120 --> 06:08.120
and no matter
what I was going through --

06:08.120 --> 06:10.580
breakup with a boyfriend,
struggling at school --

06:10.580 --> 06:13.920
no matter what, he just would
tell me one of those stories

06:13.920 --> 06:16.540
and somehow make it
apply to my life.

06:16.540 --> 06:18.210
[ Chuckling ]
I couldn't stand them.

06:18.210 --> 06:20.460
I thought
they were so boring.

06:20.460 --> 06:22.750
But now I'd kill
to have him rattle them off

06:22.750 --> 06:25.080
the way he used to.

06:25.080 --> 06:26.210
Hey.

06:26.210 --> 06:27.750
♪♪

06:27.750 --> 06:29.210
Here's the lip gloss
I was telling you about.

06:31.170 --> 06:32.170
Morning.

06:32.170 --> 06:33.170
Good morning.

06:34.170 --> 06:35.420
Hey. I, um --

06:35.420 --> 06:37.580
I just got an e-mail
from your guidance counselor,

06:37.580 --> 06:41.080
just reminding you
to register for the PSATs.

06:42.500 --> 06:43.960
Thanks.

06:43.960 --> 06:46.330
♪♪

06:46.330 --> 06:47.960
Regina:
If it makes you feel any better,

06:47.960 --> 06:50.120
she didn't really need
to come in this morning.

06:50.120 --> 06:54.290
Maybe she knew you'd be here
and wanted a little contact.

06:54.290 --> 06:55.580
Really?

06:55.580 --> 06:58.040
If nothing else,
you didn't yell at each other.

06:58.040 --> 06:59.670
[ Chuckles ]

06:59.670 --> 07:01.830
That's the bar?
Not yelling at each other?

07:01.830 --> 07:03.540
[ Chuckles ]

07:03.540 --> 07:06.210
You're right.
I'll take it.

07:06.210 --> 07:08.670
We just thought you might
want to talk with someone

07:08.670 --> 07:10.540
about what
you've been going through.

07:10.540 --> 07:12.960
I'm not
going through anything.

07:12.960 --> 07:15.790
I already apologized to Auggie
for pushing him at school.

07:15.790 --> 07:16.830
I had my consequence,

07:16.830 --> 07:19.210
and I don't need
to talk about it anymore.

07:19.210 --> 07:21.500
Actually, T...

07:21.500 --> 07:23.420
the reason why
I asked Dad

07:23.420 --> 07:26.210
if I could take you
to meet Susan today was...

07:26.210 --> 07:28.920
'cause I was hoping
that I could talk to her

07:28.920 --> 07:30.880
about some of the stuff
going on in my life.

07:30.880 --> 07:33.330
You have stuff
to talk about?

07:33.330 --> 07:34.670
Oh, sure.

07:34.670 --> 07:36.460
I mean, everybody does.

07:36.460 --> 07:37.790
There's nothing wrong
with that.

07:37.790 --> 07:41.420
Yeah, so, maybe I'll talk to her
about what I'm feeling,

07:41.420 --> 07:44.790
and you don't have to say
anything if you don't want.

07:44.790 --> 07:46.380
Just be there.

07:46.380 --> 07:48.170
Okay?
So I'm not alone.

07:50.000 --> 07:52.500
Okay.
If it will help you.

07:52.500 --> 07:54.290
Thanks, T.

07:55.960 --> 07:58.420
[ Chuckles softly ]

08:00.000 --> 08:02.420
Jake! Can you get
the lamb shanks?

08:03.380 --> 08:04.960
Jake?

08:04.960 --> 08:05.960
I'll get the lamb.

08:05.960 --> 08:07.040
Thanks.

08:09.170 --> 08:10.620
Jake,
what are you doing?

08:10.620 --> 08:11.920
Uh...
no, I was just --

08:11.920 --> 08:14.580
I asked her to help me
with something, and...

08:14.580 --> 08:16.250
um...

08:16.250 --> 08:18.830
Okay. Yeah.
Uh, thanks.

08:18.830 --> 08:27.380
♪♪

08:31.750 --> 08:33.460
Rome:
Okay, babe, we're rolling.

08:33.460 --> 08:34.830
Let's -- Hi? [ Chuckles ]
What's going on?

08:34.830 --> 08:37.250
Oh, nothing.
Just, uh, we got the call.

08:37.250 --> 08:38.420
Hmm.

08:38.420 --> 08:39.960
The call, baby.

08:39.960 --> 08:42.420
A birth mother
wants to meet with us.

08:42.420 --> 08:43.500
No.

08:43.500 --> 08:45.420
Are you serious?

08:45.420 --> 08:46.880
[ Voice breaking ]
Are you serious?

08:46.880 --> 08:48.580
I'm very serious.

08:48.580 --> 08:50.540
[ Laughs ]
Stop it.

08:50.540 --> 08:51.540
[ Beep ]

08:51.540 --> 08:53.920
Look at her.
Gary: Look at you.

08:53.920 --> 08:56.170
I'm putting together a montage
that the baby can watch one day.

08:56.170 --> 08:57.620
It will be
my masterpiece.

08:57.620 --> 08:58.750
Wow.

08:58.750 --> 09:00.540
You give your child
the next "Citizen Kane,"

09:00.540 --> 09:03.170
and all I've given mine
is stress and anxiety.

09:03.170 --> 09:04.330
How is the little man?

09:04.330 --> 09:06.040
You gotta make sure
he's all fixed and proper

09:06.040 --> 09:07.420
before I become
his guardian.

09:07.420 --> 09:11.500
Katherine is taking him to
his first therapy session today.

09:11.500 --> 09:14.790
I just...wish there was
more I could do to help.

09:14.790 --> 09:16.620
Nah, seriously, dude.
You got him the help, right?

09:16.620 --> 09:17.830
That's not nothing.

09:19.000 --> 09:20.830
Yes, RuPaul?
Why are you
all dressed up?

09:20.830 --> 09:23.170
You got a hot date
or a court appearance?

09:23.170 --> 09:25.120
No, it's a friend's
cancer remission party.

09:25.120 --> 09:26.790
Actually,
I wasn't gonna go...

09:26.790 --> 09:28.620
'til Maggie
talked me into it.

09:30.830 --> 09:32.750
Maggie talked you
into it?

09:32.750 --> 09:33.920
You talked to Maggie?

09:33.920 --> 09:35.250
Yeah, after all the Eric stuff
went down,

09:35.250 --> 09:37.000
I went over there
and made sure she was okay.

09:37.000 --> 09:38.170
You were
in her apartment?

09:38.170 --> 09:39.500
You have never been
in a woman's apartment

09:39.500 --> 09:40.830
without having sex
with her.

09:40.830 --> 09:42.170
No, no, no,
there was the one time

09:42.170 --> 09:44.000
the boyfriend came home
before Gary's boxers came off.

09:44.000 --> 09:45.380
Yes.

09:45.380 --> 09:46.960
You are doing
an infidelity joke with me?

09:46.960 --> 09:48.580
Stay on topic.
You and Maggie.

09:48.580 --> 09:49.670
Yeah.
How was that?

09:49.670 --> 09:51.250
I mean, Eric is
out of the picture, right?

09:51.250 --> 09:52.790
This is why
the party's gonna suck.

09:52.790 --> 09:54.710
Everybody's gonna want to know
why we're not together anymore,

09:54.710 --> 09:56.080
and I don't want
to keep talking about it.

09:56.080 --> 09:57.790
I can tell you guys
to screw off,

09:57.790 --> 09:59.420
but you know
what's really hard?

09:59.420 --> 10:03.790
Telling people who've had cancer
to go screw themselves.

10:03.790 --> 10:05.000
I mean, I'll do it.

10:05.000 --> 10:06.080
[ Chuckles ]

10:06.080 --> 10:08.120
Maggie: I'm not sure
that's right.

10:08.120 --> 10:09.290
Too much?
Mnh...

10:09.290 --> 10:10.670
I don't want
to look like

10:10.670 --> 10:12.540
I'm trying too hard
to impress Eve, but...

10:12.540 --> 10:13.920
But you want
to impress Eve.

10:13.920 --> 10:15.330
Yes, I do.
Mm-hmm.

10:15.330 --> 10:16.790
Mnh-mnh.
Ohh...

10:16.790 --> 10:18.790
Hey,
what about this one?

10:18.790 --> 10:20.580
Oh, that's Rome's.

10:22.250 --> 10:23.750
He is his own person.

10:23.750 --> 10:25.080
Yeah.

10:25.080 --> 10:27.790
So, anyway, um...

10:27.790 --> 10:29.420
yeah, Gary...
Yeah.

10:29.420 --> 10:32.420
...stopped by to check on me
after all the Eric stuff.

10:32.420 --> 10:33.500
So, therefore...

10:33.500 --> 10:35.330
No.
Mm-hmm.
A little bit.

10:35.330 --> 10:36.670
Gina.
Okay.

10:36.670 --> 10:38.170
[ Both chuckle ]

10:38.170 --> 10:40.420
The stuff with Gary
was just so messed up,

10:40.420 --> 10:42.750
and I've spent
the last three months

10:42.750 --> 10:46.120
with a guy who was lying to me
from the moment we met.

10:46.120 --> 10:48.500
I just can't keep...

10:48.500 --> 10:50.750
Aw. What is it?

10:52.250 --> 10:54.210
You know,
if you asked me right now

10:54.210 --> 10:56.000
do I want
to get back with Gary,

10:56.000 --> 10:57.170
I don't.

10:57.170 --> 11:00.170
But there is something
really incredible about how

11:00.170 --> 11:02.420
he was there for me
as a friend the other night,

11:02.420 --> 11:04.000
and that's what I miss.

11:04.000 --> 11:06.670
But I don't know
if I can have that,

11:06.670 --> 11:10.620
and I don't know if it's fair
for me to ask him to be that.

11:10.620 --> 11:13.710
And honestly, I don't even know
if we can do that.

11:13.710 --> 11:16.420
♪♪

11:16.420 --> 11:19.330
Katherine: So, I have been
working on this case for months.

11:19.330 --> 11:22.250
Then when it went to trial,
they took it away from me,

11:22.250 --> 11:24.250
gave it
to another lawyer.

11:24.250 --> 11:25.380
Ted.

11:25.380 --> 11:28.120
I was sad
and a little mad.

11:28.120 --> 11:29.670
Maybe a lot mad.

11:31.330 --> 11:33.920
Because I had worked
so hard

11:33.920 --> 11:37.210
and this was
a big, big change.

11:38.710 --> 11:40.880
Susan:
What did you do?

11:40.880 --> 11:45.000
I smiled
and said, "Okay."

11:45.000 --> 11:47.420
Even though
it didn't feel okay.

11:47.420 --> 11:48.750
Did you tell
anyone at work

11:48.750 --> 11:50.580
that you were unhappy
with the decision?

11:50.580 --> 11:52.710
Well, no.

11:52.710 --> 11:55.710
I didn't want the guys to think
I was being difficult.

11:55.710 --> 11:58.000
Do you think you were taken off
the case because you're a woman?

11:59.210 --> 12:00.920
I...

12:03.580 --> 12:05.670
I have my suspicions.

12:05.670 --> 12:07.880
The firm is going through
a management shake-up,

12:07.880 --> 12:10.960
and I didn't want
to add to the tension

12:10.960 --> 12:12.250
by complaining.

12:12.250 --> 12:13.620
I get that.

12:13.620 --> 12:19.000
♪♪

12:19.000 --> 12:20.580
Do you agree
with your mom, Theo?

12:20.580 --> 12:21.750
Yeah.

12:21.750 --> 12:23.710
If you complain
about a problem,

12:23.710 --> 12:25.920
you're just making
more of a problem.

12:25.920 --> 12:28.210
♪♪

12:28.210 --> 12:30.380
Check this out.

12:30.380 --> 12:32.420
That's great, sweetie.

12:32.420 --> 12:39.250
♪♪

12:39.250 --> 12:41.830
[ Indistinct conversation ]

12:41.830 --> 12:42.960
Delilah: Sophie!

12:42.960 --> 12:44.960
Hey,
I thought maybe, uh...
Oh, God.

12:44.960 --> 12:46.620
...I could give you
a ride home.

12:46.620 --> 12:48.330
Please?

12:48.330 --> 12:49.500
After this morning,

12:49.500 --> 12:52.460
I thought maybe we could
have a little...check-in.

12:52.460 --> 12:53.620
Yeah, well, I-I don't.

12:53.620 --> 12:55.080
Especially not with you.

12:55.080 --> 12:56.920
Alright, S-Soph,
come on, please.

12:56.920 --> 12:58.460
Let's just --
Talk to me.

12:58.460 --> 13:00.710
I'm still your mother.

13:00.710 --> 13:01.830
Look, it's just...

13:01.830 --> 13:03.790
Jake is almost 19,
and I don't --

13:03.790 --> 13:05.620
Look, no, you do not
get to talk to me

13:05.620 --> 13:07.920
about who it's okay
to have a relationship with.

13:07.920 --> 13:10.790
I mean [Scoffs]
seriously?

13:10.790 --> 13:12.040
Sophie --
No. No, no, no.

13:12.040 --> 13:14.620
You want to talk about this?
Let's talk about this.

13:14.620 --> 13:16.830
You cheated on him.

13:16.830 --> 13:19.120
He was always there for you,
and you cheated on him.

13:19.120 --> 13:20.790
I know. I know.
Just stop.

13:20.790 --> 13:22.380
Stop.

13:22.380 --> 13:23.500
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

13:23.500 --> 13:25.620
I messed up,
but you can't just keep on --

13:25.620 --> 13:27.500
[ Sighing ] God.

13:27.500 --> 13:28.500
[ Cellphone beeps ]
One second.

13:28.500 --> 13:29.670
Hello?

13:29.670 --> 13:31.000
Yes, this is she.

13:31.960 --> 13:33.670
What? What do you mean
he's missing?

13:34.710 --> 13:36.420
Okay, I'll be right there.
I'll be right there.

13:36.420 --> 13:38.170
Thank you. Bye.

13:38.170 --> 13:39.750
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Oh, God.
Okay, I have to go.

13:39.750 --> 13:41.170
Wait, what's going on?
They can't find Poppa.

13:41.170 --> 13:42.960
I just --
I need to go right now.

13:42.960 --> 13:45.460
♪♪

13:45.460 --> 13:47.380
[ Car door closes ]
What are you doing?

13:47.380 --> 13:48.960
I'm helping you
find Poppa.

13:48.960 --> 13:49.960
Let's go.

13:49.960 --> 13:51.830
[ Seatbelt clicks ]

13:51.830 --> 13:54.210
♪♪

13:58.580 --> 13:59.880
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:59.880 --> 14:01.330
Um...

14:05.120 --> 14:06.250
[ Chuckles ]

14:06.250 --> 14:07.710
Babe, too much teeth.

14:07.710 --> 14:09.670
Hi. I'm Eve.
Don't get up.
Don't get up.

14:09.670 --> 14:11.080
Okay.
I mean,
unless you have to pee.

14:11.080 --> 14:12.620
If you have to pee, let me --
let me help you up.

14:12.620 --> 14:15.960
This is my awkward,
yet adorable husband, Rome.

14:15.960 --> 14:17.120
And I'm Regina.

14:17.120 --> 14:19.120
And you're the Howards!

14:19.120 --> 14:20.500
[ Laughter ]

14:20.500 --> 14:22.830
I loved your video. It was like
watching a reality show.

14:22.830 --> 14:24.500
No, that's good.

14:24.500 --> 14:25.830
That's good.
[ Chuckles ]

14:25.830 --> 14:26.880
Please.

14:29.210 --> 14:30.500
And by the way, Rome,

14:30.500 --> 14:32.750
I think you're showing
just the right amount of teeth.

14:32.750 --> 14:33.880
Thank you.
[ Chuckles ]

14:33.880 --> 14:36.420
Your man's got nice teeth.
Let him show 'em off.

14:36.420 --> 14:37.750
I tend to smile a lot

14:37.750 --> 14:39.290
when I'm nervous
and want things to go well.

14:39.290 --> 14:40.500
Yeah, I bite my nails.

14:40.500 --> 14:42.420
Which is what I've been doing
all morning,

14:42.420 --> 14:43.710
waiting for this meeting.

14:43.710 --> 14:46.540
It is a bad habit
'cause my nails are fake.

14:46.540 --> 14:48.380
Fake nails
and a real baby.

14:48.380 --> 14:49.670
[ Chuckling ]
That's my story.

14:49.670 --> 14:51.380
Well, look, thank you
for meeting with us.

14:52.460 --> 14:54.290
Thank you for coming
all the way out to Brighton.

14:54.290 --> 14:55.460
You know,
it wasn't a problem.

14:55.460 --> 14:56.920
I actually grew up
not too far from here.

14:56.920 --> 14:59.250
Oh.
And you're originally
from Philly?

14:59.250 --> 15:01.750
Yeah.
Moved a few months ago.

15:01.750 --> 15:03.460
Oh.
How do you like Boston?

15:03.460 --> 15:04.750
I like it.

15:04.750 --> 15:06.620
Although, I haven't been able
to find a decent hoagie.

15:06.620 --> 15:08.380
Uh, that's because
you're calling it a hoagie.

15:08.380 --> 15:09.620
In Boston,
it's called a sub.

15:09.620 --> 15:10.920
Yeah, I won't hold that one
against you.

15:10.920 --> 15:12.250
[ Laughter ]

15:12.250 --> 15:14.250
What do we say
we get some coffee?

15:14.250 --> 15:16.420
I mean, decaf for you,
obviously, Eve.

15:16.420 --> 15:19.080
Uh -- That's okay.
I'll get it.

15:20.250 --> 15:21.750
[ Groans ]

15:21.750 --> 15:23.750
[ Whispering ]
You asked our birth mother
to get us coffee?

15:23.750 --> 15:26.170
[ Whispering ] I didn't know
that she worked here.

15:26.170 --> 15:27.420
Wait.

15:28.920 --> 15:30.080
Are you saying...

15:30.080 --> 15:32.460
She could really be
our birth mother.

15:32.460 --> 15:37.120
♪♪

15:37.120 --> 15:39.500
But when I came down
to pick him up for tea,

15:39.500 --> 15:41.000
his door
was wide open --

15:41.000 --> 15:42.670
Okay.
Thank you, Abigail.

15:42.670 --> 15:44.500
Oh, I do hope
he's alright.

15:44.500 --> 15:46.830
I mean, he's so sweet.

15:46.830 --> 15:48.420
He has such nice hands.

15:48.420 --> 15:50.330
[ Knock on door ]

15:50.330 --> 15:52.330
We did a sweep of the grounds
and haven't located him yet.

15:52.330 --> 15:53.830
Karen: Thanks, Wayne.

15:53.830 --> 15:56.540
I know this is upsetting,
but while this sort of thing

15:56.540 --> 15:59.380
does happen on a rare occasion
here at Springbrook Hills,

15:59.380 --> 16:01.500
the resident always turns up
safe and sound.

16:01.500 --> 16:02.830
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

16:02.830 --> 16:05.250
Bravo for Springbrook Hills.

16:05.250 --> 16:07.580
Can we just please --
just try to find him?

16:07.580 --> 16:08.670
Find my father?

16:08.670 --> 16:10.210
Why don't you come down
to the office?

16:10.210 --> 16:11.670
We'll review
the security footage.

16:11.670 --> 16:15.170
♪♪

16:15.170 --> 16:17.380
Soph, why don't you just
stay here, just in case?

16:17.380 --> 16:18.620
No,
but I want to help.

16:18.620 --> 16:20.540
No, just -- please.
Just -- please.

16:20.540 --> 16:22.710
Just in case
he comes back.

16:22.710 --> 16:23.960
What's weird is,

16:23.960 --> 16:25.920
I eat the exact same amount
as before I was pregnant.

16:25.920 --> 16:27.830
It's like I've been
eating for two my whole life.

16:27.830 --> 16:30.790
[ Both chuckle ]

16:30.790 --> 16:33.670
I guess I'm just not ready
to be a mom.

16:33.670 --> 16:35.830
And I don't have the support
system you both have.

16:35.830 --> 16:38.000
All that stuff
from your friends and family --

16:38.000 --> 16:39.330
it really moved me.

16:39.330 --> 16:42.580
I mean, it helps that I have
all these extra hormones in me,

16:42.580 --> 16:46.000
making me cry and eat pie
and yell at a puppy.

16:46.000 --> 16:47.750
[ Laughter ]

16:47.750 --> 16:51.000
But overall,
I guess I'm in good shape.

16:51.000 --> 16:54.420
I'm not gonna lie,
the first trimester was tough.

16:54.420 --> 16:57.170
I mean,
I was throwing up into --

16:58.920 --> 16:59.960
I'm sorry.

16:59.960 --> 17:01.920
I know not everyone
is able to --

17:01.920 --> 17:03.670
Oh, no. We never tried
to get pregnant.

17:03.670 --> 17:05.460
This is
what we want to do.

17:05.460 --> 17:07.420
This is our first choice.
You are our first choice.

17:07.420 --> 17:08.540
[ Chuckles ]

17:08.540 --> 17:09.790
Oh, I forgot.

17:09.790 --> 17:13.750
Uh, we wanted to ask you
about the birth father.

17:13.750 --> 17:15.750
You put down...

17:15.750 --> 17:17.420
"Father unknown."

17:17.420 --> 17:19.330
What does that mean,
exactly?

17:19.330 --> 17:21.330
♪♪

17:21.330 --> 17:24.580
I-I do know who the father is.
He's just not in my life.

17:24.580 --> 17:26.960
No, no. We just -- We
just want to know as much
about him as we can.

17:26.960 --> 17:28.830
You know, medical history,
that type of stuff.

17:28.830 --> 17:30.250
Yeah,
it's kind of important.

17:30.250 --> 17:32.540
Yeah. Of course.
Um...

17:32.540 --> 17:34.750
He's healthy,
as far as I know.

17:34.750 --> 17:36.540
No drugs or cigarettes.

17:36.540 --> 17:38.380
Uh, played baseball
in high school.

17:38.380 --> 17:40.460
When was the last time
you saw him?

17:40.460 --> 17:41.670
Not since I got pregnant.

17:41.670 --> 17:44.500
You know, we only...
saw each other a few times.

17:44.500 --> 17:47.170
But trust me,

17:47.170 --> 17:50.500
I don't think he'd want
anything to do with the baby.

17:50.500 --> 17:55.500
♪♪

17:55.500 --> 17:57.670
So, I would say
number one is reading

17:57.670 --> 17:59.710
and number two
is LEGOs.

17:59.710 --> 18:03.420
But I didn't see any books
on your shelf that I liked.

18:03.420 --> 18:04.460
No offense.

18:04.460 --> 18:06.540
None taken.

18:06.540 --> 18:08.170
What are you
making there?

18:08.170 --> 18:09.460
A space ship.

18:09.460 --> 18:12.170
I like these because
you can build whatever you want.

18:12.170 --> 18:14.790
But I have to keep all
the pieces cleaned up at home

18:14.790 --> 18:16.500
because Charlie
might eat them.

18:16.500 --> 18:17.750
[ Chuckles ]

18:17.750 --> 18:21.120
And what's Charlie like,
besides being a LEGO eater?

18:21.120 --> 18:22.750
She's great.

18:22.750 --> 18:25.620
I can't wait to have
some conversations with her.

18:25.620 --> 18:30.000
Right now,
it's mostly just, "Hi. Hey."

18:30.000 --> 18:31.670
I got a lot more to say.

18:31.670 --> 18:33.710
I'll bet you do.

18:33.710 --> 18:36.460
It must be great
having her around.

18:36.460 --> 18:38.250
But I bet
sometimes it seems like

18:38.250 --> 18:40.750
a lot of change
all of a sudden.

18:40.750 --> 18:43.080
How does it
make you feel?

18:43.080 --> 18:44.880
It's good.

18:44.880 --> 18:46.000
I'm okay.

18:46.000 --> 18:47.250
Great.

18:47.250 --> 18:50.670
But, honey, it'd be natural
to have lots of feelings

18:50.670 --> 18:52.670
about something like
a new baby in the house.

18:53.710 --> 18:57.330
No. It's okay. Really.

18:57.330 --> 18:59.040
You don't have to worry
about me.

18:59.040 --> 19:01.960
♪♪

19:01.960 --> 19:05.790
It's my job
to worry about you, Theo.

19:05.790 --> 19:09.250
Mom and Dad just want to
make sure you're happy, okay?

19:09.250 --> 19:12.670
♪♪

19:12.670 --> 19:14.750
You know you deserve
to be happy, right?

19:16.330 --> 19:18.000
I don't know.

19:18.000 --> 19:21.380
♪♪

19:21.380 --> 19:24.750
[ Indistinct conversations ]

19:30.170 --> 19:31.540
Hello, Bloom.

19:31.540 --> 19:33.500
Fancy meeting you here.

19:33.500 --> 19:35.420
That's a killer dress.
You look beautiful.

19:35.420 --> 19:36.750
Thanks.
You -- You do, too.

19:36.750 --> 19:38.420
I mean -- Th--
Not...

19:38.420 --> 19:40.250
Handsome -- You get it.
...beautiful.

19:40.250 --> 19:42.210
It's a nice dress.
You look...

19:42.210 --> 19:43.670
Great jacke--
...nice.

19:43.670 --> 19:44.920
[ Elevator bell dings ]

19:44.920 --> 19:46.960
It's Danny's.
[ Chuckles ]

19:46.960 --> 19:47.960
Mm.

19:47.960 --> 19:50.120
[ Clears throat ]

19:55.750 --> 19:58.750
[ Elevator doors close ]

19:58.750 --> 20:01.000
[ Sniffs ]

20:01.000 --> 20:02.380
[ Clears throat ]

20:10.880 --> 20:12.830
My ears are popping.
Are your ears popping?

20:14.330 --> 20:15.420
No.

20:19.170 --> 20:20.540
[ Elevator bell dings ]

20:20.540 --> 20:22.500
[ Indistinct conversations ]
[ Sighs ]

20:22.500 --> 20:24.250
Buckle up.

20:24.250 --> 20:27.420
♪♪

20:27.420 --> 20:29.670
There they are!
[ Laughs ]

20:29.670 --> 20:30.920
Hi.

20:30.920 --> 20:32.420
Oh, there she is.

20:32.420 --> 20:33.460
Five years.

20:33.460 --> 20:42.750
♪♪

20:42.750 --> 20:47.670
♪♪

20:47.670 --> 20:48.880
[ Chuckles ]

20:48.880 --> 20:50.790
[ Refrigerator door closes ]

20:50.790 --> 20:53.170
So, while we review
the security footage,

20:53.170 --> 20:54.830
the police have his photo,

20:54.830 --> 20:57.080
and they'll alert us
if --
Whoa. Look at camera 4.
Isn't that --

20:57.080 --> 20:58.290
My daughter.

20:58.290 --> 20:59.960
Sophie.

20:59.960 --> 21:02.500
What is she doing?

21:02.500 --> 21:04.830
[ Tires squeal ]

21:04.830 --> 21:06.290
Sophie!

21:06.290 --> 21:07.710
Sophie, wait!
[ Engine revs ]

21:12.580 --> 21:15.580
[ Indistinct conversations ]

21:19.120 --> 21:20.620
Hey, Poppa.

21:20.620 --> 21:22.580
Oh.
Hey, there, kiddo.

21:22.580 --> 21:23.960
[ Chuckles ]

21:23.960 --> 21:26.670
I can't remember
what I came in here for.

21:26.670 --> 21:27.750
[ Sighs ]

21:27.750 --> 21:28.960
Well, while we're here,

21:28.960 --> 21:31.000
what do you say
we pick up some fennel sausage,

21:31.000 --> 21:33.330
since it's Pizza Friday?

21:33.330 --> 21:34.500
Oh. Yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

21:34.500 --> 21:35.830
Right. Of course.

21:35.830 --> 21:38.250
I was making pizza.

21:38.250 --> 21:40.080
What do you say we get some
and get home?

21:40.080 --> 21:41.420
Yes.
[ Chuckles ]

21:41.420 --> 21:42.500
Yes.

21:42.500 --> 21:43.750
[ Chuckles ]

21:43.750 --> 21:46.170
I saw you arrive together.
So...?

21:46.170 --> 21:48.790
No. Sorry.
Still broken up.

21:48.790 --> 21:51.120
Ohhh. Uh...

21:51.120 --> 21:52.790
No. Hey.
It's all good.

21:52.790 --> 21:55.500
I could have told you.
Gary's allergic to commitment.

21:55.500 --> 21:56.420
Ohh!
[ Laughs ]

21:56.420 --> 21:58.000
There's no EpiPen
for that.

21:58.000 --> 21:59.000
You know, Kay --

21:59.000 --> 22:00.580
Actually, um,
it was me.

22:00.580 --> 22:02.330
I-I couldn't commit
to him.

22:02.330 --> 22:03.330
[ Chuckles ]

22:03.330 --> 22:05.040
Oh, Gary.

22:05.040 --> 22:08.540
Well, what'd you do to make it
so poor Maggie couldn't commit?

22:08.540 --> 22:09.380
Mm.

22:09.380 --> 22:10.500
[ Laughter ]

22:10.500 --> 22:12.420
I'm gonna mosey on over

22:12.420 --> 22:14.250
to what I'm praying
is an open bar.

22:14.250 --> 22:18.540
♪♪

22:18.540 --> 22:20.420
He's gone. Spill it.

22:20.420 --> 22:21.420
Yeah.

22:21.420 --> 22:24.420
♪♪

22:24.420 --> 22:28.170
I like what a nice, big,
safe car this is.

22:28.170 --> 22:29.330
[ Chuckles, taps door ]

22:30.330 --> 22:32.750
Oh, right. It was
a birthday gift from Jon.

22:36.210 --> 22:38.710
I'm sorry. I didn't mean, uh,
to upset you by mentioning him.

22:38.710 --> 22:40.000
I --
Oh, no.

22:40.000 --> 22:42.330
No, no, no, it's --
it's okay.

22:42.330 --> 22:44.710
Have you talked to him,
like you said you were going to?

22:44.710 --> 22:46.580
♪♪

22:46.580 --> 22:47.620
Have you?

22:47.620 --> 22:49.250
Uh...

22:49.250 --> 22:50.920
No, he's...

22:50.920 --> 22:52.830
Look, honey,
I know I'm your dad,

22:52.830 --> 22:57.170
and I know it's not my place
to get involved, but...

22:57.170 --> 22:59.880
you can't go on
living like this.

23:01.920 --> 23:04.000
Feeling so alone
in your marriage.

23:04.000 --> 23:07.170
I mean, if he refuses to admit
there's a problem,

23:07.170 --> 23:11.670
if he's unwilling to acknowledge
his own wife is unhappy...

23:11.670 --> 23:12.710
I'm not --

23:12.710 --> 23:15.670
DeeDee...
don't say it's for the kids,

23:15.670 --> 23:19.250
because
you're their role model.

23:19.250 --> 23:21.380
I mean, don't you want Sophie
to grow up knowing

23:21.380 --> 23:24.920
that she has a right to be happy
in her own marriage?

23:24.920 --> 23:27.120
♪♪

23:27.120 --> 23:28.500
Yeah.

23:28.500 --> 23:31.210
I know you're trying to keep up
a perfect front for the family.

23:31.210 --> 23:32.210
[ Chuckles ]

23:32.210 --> 23:34.790
Lord knows
he doesn't make it easy.

23:34.790 --> 23:37.790
He may be a good father,

23:37.790 --> 23:41.330
but for
more than a while now,

23:41.330 --> 23:43.330
he hasn't been
a great husband.

23:44.880 --> 23:47.120
I just want my daughter
to be happy.

23:47.120 --> 23:50.580
♪♪

23:50.580 --> 23:52.750
[ Indistinct conversations ]

23:52.750 --> 23:54.880
Gary: Kay introduced me
to her husband

23:54.880 --> 23:57.920
as "the guy who broke
Maggie Bloom's heart."

23:57.920 --> 24:01.290
So...
sorry about that.

24:01.290 --> 24:02.420
You know what?

24:02.420 --> 24:04.080
We are doing this
for Elena.
Mm-hmm.

24:04.080 --> 24:07.000
So, pull up your big-boy pants,
make some small talk with me,

24:07.000 --> 24:09.250
and then turn to your left
and do it all over again.

24:09.250 --> 24:11.500
Okay. Small talk.

24:11.500 --> 24:13.830
Oh. Got a job interview
next week.

24:13.830 --> 24:14.920
Fingers crossed.
Mm!

24:14.920 --> 24:17.170
Saw my mom for the first time
in 28 years.

24:17.170 --> 24:19.080
Got my car washed.
Bought the 10 pack.

24:19.080 --> 24:20.170
Wait, what?

24:20.170 --> 24:21.920
Financially,
it makes more sense, Bloom.

24:21.920 --> 24:24.040
No, you saw your mom?

24:24.040 --> 24:25.250
What --

24:25.250 --> 24:27.750
What did she say?
What did you guys talk about?

24:27.750 --> 24:29.330
A lot.

24:29.330 --> 24:30.540
And nothing.

24:30.540 --> 24:31.710
Got what I needed,

24:31.710 --> 24:33.790
all thanks
to a certain miniature person

24:33.790 --> 24:37.960
who told me I should...
work on myself.

24:37.960 --> 24:39.210
Wow.

24:39.210 --> 24:41.500
So, 28 years.
How do you feel?

24:41.500 --> 24:43.880
Oh, I'm sorry. Apparently, I
have to turn to this person now.

24:43.880 --> 24:45.000
Hey, man.

24:45.000 --> 24:46.080
Gary Mendez.

24:46.080 --> 24:47.250
I'll be honest --

24:47.250 --> 24:49.250
I've never been
a big fruit in salad guy,

24:49.250 --> 24:52.170
but these orange segments are
making me rethink everything.

24:52.170 --> 24:53.710
[ Laughter ]

24:53.710 --> 24:56.080
You're the expert,
Gloria.

24:56.080 --> 24:57.960
Does this happen a lot?

24:57.960 --> 24:59.790
[ Whispering ]
What'd she say?

25:01.830 --> 25:03.500
Is it a problem?

25:04.960 --> 25:06.920
Mm-hmm. Okay.

25:06.920 --> 25:08.830
Yeah, thank you.
We'll be in touch.

25:09.790 --> 25:10.830
[ Cellphone beeps ]

25:10.830 --> 25:12.540
[ Exhales sharply ]

25:12.540 --> 25:16.040
Gloria said not having contact
with the birth father

25:16.040 --> 25:18.250
in these situations
is fairly common.

25:18.250 --> 25:20.290
So it happens a lot.

25:20.290 --> 25:21.540
That's good, right?

25:21.540 --> 25:23.000
But if he hasn't filed

25:23.000 --> 25:25.670
parental responsibility
with the state,

25:25.670 --> 25:28.670
then he could come back
and file a legal claim.

25:28.670 --> 25:32.580
She said that's one
of the main reasons
adoptions fall through.

25:32.580 --> 25:35.460
But Eve --
she's perfect.

25:35.460 --> 25:38.420
She was perfect...

25:38.420 --> 25:41.210
until we mentioned the father
and she got all cagey.

25:41.210 --> 25:44.080
I think --
I think that she was just...

25:44.080 --> 25:45.750
embarrassed.

25:45.750 --> 25:48.420
It didn't sound like
they were a couple.

25:48.420 --> 25:49.920
Rome...

25:49.920 --> 25:51.920
this guy could swoop in
in the last minute

25:51.920 --> 25:54.330
and take our baby.

25:54.330 --> 25:56.460
I'm sorry, but...no.

25:56.460 --> 26:00.620
My gut is telling me
this is not right.
We were so lucky
to be matched so quickly.

26:00.620 --> 26:02.960
W-What if we never get
another chance?

26:02.960 --> 26:05.790
♪♪

26:05.790 --> 26:07.080
Gina.

26:09.170 --> 26:10.750
Are you looking
for a way out

26:10.750 --> 26:12.960
because maybe you are having
a change of heart?

26:12.960 --> 26:15.670
Are you kidding me?

26:15.670 --> 26:18.500
Pull up that video
from yesterday. I had tears.

26:19.960 --> 26:22.040
You ask me
if I want a baby?

26:22.040 --> 26:23.210
Of course I do.

26:23.210 --> 26:26.710
But not like this,
not jumping in blindly.

26:28.040 --> 26:30.250
Rome, the one thing
that we agreed on

26:30.250 --> 26:32.250
was that this baby
would bring us together,

26:32.250 --> 26:34.380
not tear us apart.

26:36.250 --> 26:37.670
Yeah, you're right.

26:37.670 --> 26:40.420
♪♪

26:40.420 --> 26:42.540
But you call
and tell them.

26:42.540 --> 26:44.710
'Cause I can't be the one
to turn her down.

26:44.710 --> 26:52.210
♪♪

26:57.830 --> 26:59.830
[ Engine shuts off ]
Okay.

26:59.830 --> 27:01.920
Oh, thank God.

27:01.920 --> 27:03.080
Oh.

27:03.080 --> 27:05.330
DeeDee.

27:05.330 --> 27:06.380
You okay?

27:06.380 --> 27:08.080
Oh.

27:09.170 --> 27:10.420
Yeah. I'm okay.

27:10.420 --> 27:12.500
I gotta go inside.

27:12.500 --> 27:13.830
Okay.
You need help?

27:13.830 --> 27:15.580
No, I'm fine.
I'm...

27:15.580 --> 27:16.670
[ Smooches ]

27:16.670 --> 27:18.170
I'm fine.

27:18.170 --> 27:19.710
[ Sighs ]
Okay.

27:19.710 --> 27:20.830
I'll be there in a minute.

27:22.960 --> 27:23.960
You okay?

27:23.960 --> 27:25.960
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]
Yeah, I'm fine.

27:25.960 --> 27:28.080
Look, I'm...

27:28.080 --> 27:31.580
I'm sorry that you have to
go through this with him.

27:31.580 --> 27:33.210
It must be so hard.

27:33.210 --> 27:35.830
Sometimes.

27:35.830 --> 27:38.000
Yeah, it is.

27:38.000 --> 27:40.000
But you know
what Poppa would say, right?

27:40.000 --> 27:42.420
"Don't let the trying times
get the best of you."

27:42.420 --> 27:45.500
"That reminds me of the story
of the young sergeant."

27:45.500 --> 27:47.040
[ Chuckles ]

27:47.040 --> 27:51.920
♪♪

27:51.920 --> 27:53.750
Katherine:
I caused it, Eddie.

27:53.750 --> 27:55.500
I mean...nature, nurture,

27:55.500 --> 27:57.040
either way,
I made him who he is.

27:57.040 --> 27:58.540
Katie,
this is not your fault.

27:58.540 --> 28:00.670
You know, Susan...

28:00.670 --> 28:02.540
asked me today...

28:02.540 --> 28:05.790
if I only fight
for my own happiness

28:05.790 --> 28:07.750
when it aligns
with everyone else's.

28:07.750 --> 28:10.710
I realized she's right.

28:10.710 --> 28:11.920
All this time,

28:11.920 --> 28:17.000
I thought I was modeling
the right behavior for Theo.

28:17.000 --> 28:19.880
I was teaching him
to...

28:19.880 --> 28:21.380
keep things in.

28:21.380 --> 28:24.080
I think we both
have been doing that.

28:26.210 --> 28:29.420
Did Susan have any advice?
Anything we can do to help?

28:29.420 --> 28:33.920
Yeah, after the session,
she said...

28:33.920 --> 28:36.580
some people,
when faced with change,

28:36.580 --> 28:39.000
pretend like
everything is okay

28:39.000 --> 28:41.290
just so they can feel
a sense of control.

28:41.290 --> 28:42.580
That's definitely Theo.

28:42.580 --> 28:45.580
So she recommended
we find small moments

28:45.580 --> 28:47.670
where he's not
in control,

28:47.670 --> 28:50.040
and we just
try to embrace it,

28:50.040 --> 28:51.540
just let it happen,

28:51.540 --> 28:55.000
let him see that the Earth
will continue to turn.

28:56.330 --> 28:57.670
Then that is what we'll do.

28:57.670 --> 28:59.670
♪♪

28:59.670 --> 29:01.460
Hey, everybody.

29:01.460 --> 29:02.580
Uh, I'm Vincent.

29:02.580 --> 29:04.620
Most of you know me
as Elena's husband.

29:04.620 --> 29:06.330
[ Chuckles ]
I'm okay with that.

29:06.330 --> 29:07.670
[ Laughter ]

29:07.670 --> 29:10.460
Six years ago,
when Lainey first started chemo,

29:10.460 --> 29:13.290
I was so...

29:13.290 --> 29:14.420
scared.

29:15.460 --> 29:17.120
But she just kept saying,

29:17.120 --> 29:19.170
"I'm gonna beat the crap
out of cancer."

29:19.170 --> 29:20.170
[ Chuckles ]

29:20.170 --> 29:22.210
So, now,
on the fifth anniversary

29:22.210 --> 29:23.620
of being in remission,

29:23.620 --> 29:27.420
I'd like to present a gift
to the strongest woman I know.

29:27.420 --> 29:29.120
[ Crowd "Aww"s ]

29:29.120 --> 29:31.080
A chance to...

29:31.080 --> 29:33.000
thanks to this piñata,
literally...

29:33.000 --> 29:34.500
[ Laughter, applause ]

29:34.500 --> 29:36.790
...beat the crap
out of cancer.

29:36.790 --> 29:38.330
[ Laughs ]

29:38.330 --> 29:39.960
[ Chuckles ]

29:39.960 --> 29:41.000
[ Laughs ]

29:41.000 --> 29:42.330
Ohh.

29:42.330 --> 29:44.460
[ Gasps ] And you know what
I'm gonna keep doing this year?

29:44.460 --> 29:46.540
Beating cancer's ass!

29:46.540 --> 29:48.540
[ Laughter, cheering ]

29:48.540 --> 29:50.830
Yes.

29:50.830 --> 29:52.420
[ Laughs ]

29:52.420 --> 29:53.460
Alright.

29:53.460 --> 29:55.210
Just gimme --
Oh!

29:55.210 --> 29:56.330
[ Laughter ]

29:56.330 --> 29:57.790
Alright,
you out of the way?

29:57.790 --> 29:59.330
Okay.

29:59.330 --> 30:00.380
[ Grunts ]

30:00.380 --> 30:02.830
[ Cheering ]

30:02.830 --> 30:04.000
[ Grunts ]

30:04.000 --> 30:04.960
Whoo!

30:04.960 --> 30:06.000
[ Applause ]

30:06.000 --> 30:07.380
Oh. No. Wait.

30:07.380 --> 30:08.750
[ Laughing ] Oh, shoot.

30:08.750 --> 30:10.750
Well, it's a good thing
I'm not playing for the Sox.

30:10.750 --> 30:13.290
[ Laughter ]

30:13.290 --> 30:14.290
[ Thud ]

30:14.290 --> 30:16.500
-Yeah!
-Yeah!
-Whoo!

30:17.500 --> 30:18.880
[ Thud ]
Vincent: Hey, babe.

30:18.880 --> 30:20.170
I can do this.
Why don't you --

30:20.170 --> 30:21.500
Wait.
No, no, no, no.

30:21.500 --> 30:23.880
I-I got it. I got -- got it.
I just -- You know --

30:23.880 --> 30:25.120
[ Exhales sharply ]

30:25.120 --> 30:27.290
I got to take this off.
I just --

30:27.290 --> 30:29.750
[ Thudding ]

30:29.750 --> 30:30.830
Come on!

30:30.830 --> 30:32.500
[ Voice breaking ]
Just...break!

30:32.500 --> 30:34.000
Just --

30:34.000 --> 30:36.500
♪♪

30:36.500 --> 30:38.000
[ Breathes shakily ]

30:38.000 --> 30:39.670
I-I can't -- I can't --

30:39.670 --> 30:41.790
I can't -- I just --
It's okay.
It doesn't matter.

30:41.790 --> 30:44.080
[ Sobbing ]
No, no, no, no.

30:45.830 --> 30:50.210
Let me...talk to Regina,
and then I'll call you back.

30:50.210 --> 30:51.960
Thanks, Gloria.

30:51.960 --> 30:52.960
[ Cellphone beeps ]

30:52.960 --> 30:55.460
Gloria?
Social worker Gloria?

30:55.460 --> 30:57.330
Eve would like
to meet with us again.

30:58.380 --> 31:01.170
She heard that we're
not moving forward and
she wants to explain.

31:01.170 --> 31:02.250
[ Sighs ]

31:02.250 --> 31:03.920
Rome, what could she
possibly say?

31:03.920 --> 31:06.080
I don't know.
Let's find out.

31:06.080 --> 31:09.080
Can we not make this
more painful than it already is?

31:09.080 --> 31:10.670
We need to move forward.

31:10.670 --> 31:12.670
That's just it.

31:12.670 --> 31:15.790
I need closure
so that we can move forward.

31:15.790 --> 31:17.790
You said it yourself --

31:17.790 --> 31:20.380
we can't let this adoption
pull us apart.

31:20.380 --> 31:26.290
♪♪

31:26.290 --> 31:30.210
[ Voice breaking ]
They told me I'd be dead
by my 45th birthday.

31:30.210 --> 31:32.330
What if
the doctors are still right?

31:32.330 --> 31:34.500
W-What if it comes back?

31:34.500 --> 31:37.000
I don't want it
to come back.

31:37.000 --> 31:39.170
[ Sobbing ]

31:41.380 --> 31:42.500
Excuse me.

31:43.880 --> 31:45.750
Elena. Hey.

31:45.750 --> 31:47.460
I get it.

31:47.460 --> 31:49.420
Even though the cancer's gone,
the fear is still there.

31:49.420 --> 31:51.830
But you cannot
let that paralyze you.

31:51.830 --> 31:53.330
You're better than that.

31:54.670 --> 31:56.250
But what if I'm not?

31:56.250 --> 31:58.830
That's why we're here.

31:58.830 --> 31:59.920
Right?

31:59.920 --> 32:01.460
-Mm-hmm.
-Yeah.
-That's right.

32:01.460 --> 32:04.830
That's why you invited all of us
to this party.

32:04.830 --> 32:08.290
When you don't feel
strong enough, we lift you up.

32:08.290 --> 32:09.460
Maggie: Yeah.

32:09.460 --> 32:10.790
-We love you.
-Yeah.
-That's right.

32:10.790 --> 32:14.040
You know, all last year,
when I was going through chemo,

32:14.040 --> 32:18.670
so many times, I thought...
I couldn't make it.

32:18.670 --> 32:20.420
And this guy
was there for me.

32:21.710 --> 32:24.170
I just helped her find the
strength I already knew she had.

32:24.170 --> 32:26.170
Gary supported me,

32:26.170 --> 32:29.080
and now we are all here
supporting you.

32:29.080 --> 32:30.620
-Yes.
-Yeah.
-Absolutely.

32:30.620 --> 32:32.420
Whether you like it
or not.

32:32.420 --> 32:33.500
[ Laughter ]

32:33.500 --> 32:35.500
Stop farting around,
take that stick...

32:35.500 --> 32:39.080
Take it, and you crack
that bottle wide open.

32:39.080 --> 32:42.290
[ Cheers and applause ]

32:42.290 --> 32:43.580
♪♪

32:43.580 --> 32:45.500
♪ When it gets heavy,
I know you get doubts ♪

32:45.500 --> 32:47.000
Get it! Yes!

32:47.000 --> 32:49.620
♪ But I'll be right here
when the sky falls down ♪

32:49.620 --> 32:51.710
Babe, you can do it!

32:51.710 --> 32:58.380
♪ I know there's always a place
for you and I ♪

32:58.380 --> 33:06.170
♪ A place where every word
that you say can save my life ♪

33:06.170 --> 33:07.420
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

33:07.420 --> 33:09.750
♪ And nothing hurts
and nothing breaks ♪

33:09.750 --> 33:10.920
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

33:10.920 --> 33:13.540
♪ I know it
when I see your face ♪

33:13.540 --> 33:14.830
♪ I'm safe ♪

33:14.830 --> 33:17.500
♪ Ohhhh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

33:17.500 --> 33:19.170
♪ I'm safe ♪

33:19.170 --> 33:21.380
♪ Ohhhh, oh, oh ♪

33:21.380 --> 33:23.040
That was amazing.

33:23.040 --> 33:24.250
♪ Ohhhh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

33:24.250 --> 33:25.250
It really was.

33:25.250 --> 33:26.420
♪ I'm safe ♪

33:26.420 --> 33:28.210
♪ Ohhhh, oh, oh ♪

33:28.210 --> 33:29.210
♪ I'm safe ♪

33:34.750 --> 33:37.710
I wasn't honest with you
this morning.

33:37.710 --> 33:39.460
And I'm sorry.

33:39.460 --> 33:41.080
I know you were concerned

33:41.080 --> 33:43.920
because I said I didn't know
where the father is.

33:43.920 --> 33:46.420
[ Voice breaking ]
But I do know where he is.

33:46.420 --> 33:49.170
I just...

33:49.170 --> 33:51.210
I don't want him to know
where I am.

33:51.210 --> 33:53.670
We were together...

33:53.670 --> 33:55.540
a year and a half.

33:55.540 --> 33:59.830
He could be so sweet...

33:59.830 --> 34:01.830
and so thoughtful.

34:05.250 --> 34:08.290
But he also has a temper,
and he --

34:08.290 --> 34:10.080
Oh, Eve.

34:11.580 --> 34:14.120
Then when I got pregnant...
[ Sniffles ]

34:14.120 --> 34:16.290
...I worried
about the baby.

34:16.290 --> 34:18.170
♪♪

34:18.170 --> 34:21.120
I could never forgive myself
if something happened.

34:21.120 --> 34:23.040
So I hid it from him.

34:24.500 --> 34:27.330
Then one day,
he just...

34:29.120 --> 34:32.580
I knew
I had to get away.

34:32.580 --> 34:35.000
I knew.

34:35.000 --> 34:37.170
And that's why
I picked you.

34:37.170 --> 34:38.750
I saw in your profile

34:38.750 --> 34:40.750
that you were on the board
of a woman's shelter,

34:40.750 --> 34:43.080
and I just --

34:43.080 --> 34:45.790
I just knew
maybe it was meant to be.

34:47.670 --> 34:49.670
I'm so sorry
for lying to you.

34:49.670 --> 34:52.580
No, no, don't apologize
for doing what you have to do

34:52.580 --> 34:55.080
to keep you
and your baby safe.

34:55.080 --> 34:56.040
Ever.

34:56.040 --> 34:58.290
[ Sniffles ]

34:58.290 --> 35:04.620
♪♪

35:05.620 --> 35:07.500
This is really good,
Mom.

35:07.500 --> 35:09.000
Thanks, sweetie.

35:09.000 --> 35:10.460
Glad you like it.

35:13.620 --> 35:14.790
Oh, no!

35:14.790 --> 35:15.960
Ohh!

35:15.960 --> 35:17.500
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.
It's okay.

35:17.500 --> 35:19.170
It's okay, T.

35:19.170 --> 35:22.080
Hey, buddy. Hey,
this is not a big deal, okay?

35:22.080 --> 35:23.960
It's alright.

35:28.330 --> 35:29.670
[ Clears throat ]

35:34.500 --> 35:36.500
Uh, let me help
with that, okay?

35:39.960 --> 35:42.750
♪♪

35:42.750 --> 35:44.170
Oh.

35:44.170 --> 35:45.790
A sneak attack, huh?

35:45.790 --> 35:47.920
[ Both chuckle ]

35:47.920 --> 35:49.540
Alright.

35:49.540 --> 35:51.330
♪♪

35:51.330 --> 35:53.330
You wouldn't dare.
Oh.

35:53.330 --> 35:56.210
[ Laughs ]

35:56.210 --> 35:57.670
[ Laughs ]

35:57.670 --> 35:59.710
Are you just gonna let
him do that to your
dear, innocent mother?

35:59.710 --> 36:01.580
♪♪

36:01.580 --> 36:03.500
Come on.

36:03.500 --> 36:04.540
Bud.

36:04.540 --> 36:05.830
Mm-hmm.

36:07.290 --> 36:08.670
Hah! [ Laughs ]
Yes!
Ohh!

36:08.670 --> 36:13.080
You brought broccoli into it,
you little stinker?!

36:13.080 --> 36:15.290
Better not touch.
It's 1 on 2.

36:15.290 --> 36:23.040
♪♪

36:23.040 --> 36:30.750
♪♪

36:30.750 --> 36:32.170
Gotta get home.

36:32.170 --> 36:35.170
Danny's been on Charlie duty
all afternoon.

36:36.460 --> 36:39.500
I'll drop you off
at Rome and Gina's.

36:39.500 --> 36:42.250
Well, you know, I might just...
crash at the house tonight.

36:43.420 --> 36:44.670
Oh.

36:44.670 --> 36:46.670
Yeah, I mean, it's closer
than Rome and Regina's,

36:46.670 --> 36:49.880
and...plus, I want to see Danny
and the baby, so...

36:51.170 --> 36:52.420
That'd be nice.

36:53.670 --> 36:54.880
[ Elevator whirring ]

36:54.880 --> 36:57.080
That was pretty incredible,
seeing Elena like that.

36:57.080 --> 36:59.330
Yeah, it was.

36:59.330 --> 37:00.540
Pretty disappointed

37:00.540 --> 37:03.460
there wasn't any candy
in that piñata, though.

37:03.460 --> 37:04.880
Confetti?
Who does that?

37:04.880 --> 37:06.040
[ Chuckles ]

37:06.040 --> 37:09.120
You gotta give a man
a Kit Kat, a Spree...

37:09.120 --> 37:10.120
[ Chuckles ]

37:10.120 --> 37:11.880
...a Dum Dum...
[ Laughs ]

37:11.880 --> 37:13.170
...some Lemonheads...

37:13.170 --> 37:15.420
You really are twelve.
[ Chuckles ]

37:17.670 --> 37:20.670
[ Thud, whirring stops ]

37:20.670 --> 37:21.670
Oh, come on.

37:21.670 --> 37:23.670
What is it with you
and elevators?

37:23.670 --> 37:25.000
[ Button clicks ]
No way.

37:25.000 --> 37:26.960
[ Chuckles ]

37:32.330 --> 37:33.330
You know what?

37:33.330 --> 37:36.250
We stopped talking
before...

37:36.250 --> 37:38.620
I told you
about visiting my mom.

37:38.620 --> 37:41.170
But I think
what I would have said

37:41.170 --> 37:43.880
is I realized something
when I was with her,

37:43.880 --> 37:47.670
and that's that I maybe...

37:47.670 --> 37:51.500
pushed you away before
you had a chance to hurt me.

37:53.380 --> 37:56.420
I used to laugh
when Jon would say

37:56.420 --> 37:59.290
that everything happens
for a reason,

37:59.290 --> 38:02.750
and this is
gonna sound crazy.

38:03.790 --> 38:07.330
I think I got cancer
so that I could find you.

38:07.330 --> 38:10.920
♪♪

38:10.920 --> 38:15.380
I love you, Maggie Bloom.

38:15.380 --> 38:19.290
I loved you then,
and I love you now.

38:20.500 --> 38:22.330
[ Voice breaking ]
I love you.

38:22.330 --> 38:25.710
♪♪

38:25.710 --> 38:26.790
[ Elevator whirring ]

38:26.790 --> 38:28.380
Oh.
My ears are popping.

38:28.380 --> 38:29.540
[ Chuckles ]

38:29.540 --> 38:30.790
Again.

38:33.540 --> 38:34.710
[ Yawns ]

38:34.710 --> 38:35.750
Yeah.

38:35.750 --> 38:37.960
[ Elevator bell dings ]

38:37.960 --> 38:40.250
[ Sighs ]

38:40.250 --> 38:41.500
Gary, wait.

38:41.500 --> 38:44.080
After everything
that happened up there,

38:44.080 --> 38:46.210
I-I realized...

38:46.210 --> 38:48.000
I was wrong.

38:49.580 --> 38:51.210
Okay.

38:51.210 --> 38:53.290
We can...
just be friends.

38:54.670 --> 38:56.620
That's crazy.

38:56.620 --> 38:58.500
I was just thinking
the same thing.

38:58.500 --> 39:01.330
♪♪

39:01.330 --> 39:02.580
Good.

39:02.580 --> 39:04.170
♪♪

39:04.170 --> 39:07.210
Sophie:
Let me tell you a story
about a young sergeant

39:07.210 --> 39:10.420
and about never giving up.

39:10.420 --> 39:13.120
The sergeant
was stationed overseas

39:13.120 --> 39:15.380
when he met a beautiful
dark-haired young woman

39:15.380 --> 39:17.170
working at a flower shop.

39:17.170 --> 39:20.880
So every few days, he'd go
into the shop to buy daisies,

39:20.880 --> 39:23.620
just so he could have an excuse
to talk to her.

39:23.620 --> 39:24.750
He made her laugh,

39:24.750 --> 39:26.960
and she made him
weak in the knees.

39:26.960 --> 39:29.080
Now, he wanted
to ask the woman out,

39:29.080 --> 39:31.880
but he just couldn't
work up the nerve.

39:31.880 --> 39:34.460
♪♪

39:34.460 --> 39:36.500
And then one day,

39:36.500 --> 39:38.960
Sergeant Farache
was shipped back to America.

39:38.960 --> 39:41.000
♪♪

39:41.000 --> 39:43.670
If you need me to go back
with you to see Susan sometime,

39:43.670 --> 39:45.250
I will.

39:45.250 --> 39:48.380
And he was heartbroken that
he missed his chance with her,

39:48.380 --> 39:51.670
but he never gave up hope that
he would one day see her again.

39:51.670 --> 39:54.620
His family and friends,
they told him to move on,

39:54.620 --> 39:56.540
but he just couldn't
forget her.

39:56.540 --> 39:59.330
We are doing
this thing!

39:59.330 --> 40:00.420
Right?
Yes.
Yes.

40:00.420 --> 40:02.500
Yes!
Text it to Eve.

40:02.500 --> 40:04.420
[ Laughter ]

40:04.420 --> 40:09.620
Sophie: He wrote to her often,
and she wrote to him.

40:09.620 --> 40:12.420
And then, two years later,

40:12.420 --> 40:15.540
while on vacation
with her family in the States,

40:15.540 --> 40:18.080
she and the sergeant
met up again.

40:18.080 --> 40:20.670
Right here in Boston.

40:20.670 --> 40:22.920
And he brought daisies for her.

40:22.920 --> 40:25.380
She was so surprised
by the gesture.

40:25.380 --> 40:26.580
And he told her,

40:26.580 --> 40:30.000
"All the daisies
I ever bought from you

40:30.000 --> 40:31.920
were for you.

40:31.920 --> 40:33.290
I just never gave them to you

40:33.290 --> 40:34.830
because I didn't have
the nerve."

40:34.830 --> 40:37.920
And then a year later,
they got married.

40:37.920 --> 40:40.960
And a year after that,
they had a baby.

40:40.960 --> 40:48.170
♪♪

40:48.170 --> 40:51.750
And that's how
Mom got her middle name.

40:51.750 --> 40:53.710
Daisy.

40:53.710 --> 40:55.120
Delilah Daisy.

40:55.120 --> 40:57.250
DeeDee for short.

40:57.250 --> 41:00.420
Poppa never gave up
on what he loved.

41:00.420 --> 41:02.380
Which is pretty good advice.

41:02.380 --> 41:06.620
So that's why we'll always
tell that story in our family.

41:06.620 --> 41:10.290
♪♪

41:10.290 --> 41:13.250
We are doing
this thing!

41:13.250 --> 41:14.120
Right?
Yes.

41:14.120 --> 41:15.170
Yes.
Absolutely.

41:15.170 --> 41:17.000
Yes!
Whoo!
Whoo!

41:17.000 --> 41:18.710
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

41:20.580 --> 41:22.750
[ Vibrating stops,
cellphone clatters ]

41:22.750 --> 41:27.290
♪♪

41:27.290 --> 41:33.830
♪♪

41:40.960 --> 41:50.170
♪♪

41:50.170 --> 41:59.330
♪♪

41:59.330 --> 42:08.670
♪♪

42:09.670 --> 42:11.460
That's my boy!

42:11.460 --> 42:16.380
